<br>
I loved the class. LOVE IT. But I just couldn't warm to my HE. I yearned to be a gnome. Eventually at 20 I just gave up. I ran to Ak'Anon, had a guildie meet me, and transferred the stuff and dumped the HE. My gnomie is up to 16th now.<br>
<br>
I had this feeling level after level since probably 12 that I wasn't happy without being gnomic, but I had put the effort in... <br>
<br>
If you're not happy now, you're not going to be happy. Play what you want. While I check in here and I'm considering starting a character, I'll be honest, the one char rule is probably the biggest single thing stopping me. <p><table border=0 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0><tr><td><img src="http://home.tampabay.rr.com/legolaas/images/numtini-100.jpg" width="52" height="100"></td><td><table style="font-family:verdana,arial;" border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;"><A HREF="http://pub94.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN" title="<insert popup caption here>" style="color:#ff0000;font-weight:700;">Numtini Lightheart</A></td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;">46th Season Gnome of Death</td></tr><tr><td style="font-size:10pt;">Member, <A HREF="http://pub96.ezboard.com/beqcivismacto" title="Civis Macto Website" style="color:#ff0000;">Civis Macto</A></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
